# ai-lib-plans Sync Automation Rules

## Rule 1 — Sync Before Planning

Before drafting or updating planning documents in `ai-lib-plans`, run:

`bash /home/alex/ai-lib-plans/tools/sync_ai_lib_plans.sh --mode pre-plan`

If sync fails, stop planning work and resolve sync/conflict issues first.

## Rule 2 — Sync After Documentation Changes

When documentation files in `ai-lib-plans` are changed and committed, run:

`bash /home/alex/ai-lib-plans/tools/sync_ai_lib_plans.sh --mode post-doc-change --push-if-ahead`

This keeps local and remote repositories synchronized after document updates.
